      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation — RH < 1 criterion",
      "description": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) was applied to CFD shear stress and exposure time fields. Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against bench-top hemolysis measurements for the FDA pump. The relative hemolysis index RH was computed for all 5 operating conditions; all values satisfied RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. Worst-case condition identified at 3500 RPM / 4 L/min. This result was generated by the CFD hemolysis post-processing activity.",
